  "body": "# Problem\n\nIf wrong pairing code is entered , user is not able to proceed after [Next] button is hit, however the input field is not cleared and red tooltip remains for next attempts which might make user think that next attempts are not being processed by system.\n\nNOTE: if i remove the card and tap it again - field is cleared.\n\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/57310382-65926400-70f2-11e9-9954-87352814a62f.png)\n\n\n## Steps\n\n1. open status\n2. i have an account -> keycard\n3. pair the device\n4. enter wrong pairing code and do not remove the card\n5. tap next one more time with the same wrong code\n\nActual result: UI says nothing that second attempt is done , looks like user is stuck\n\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/57310788-1698fe80-70f3-11e9-8e05-146e3c1d4255.png)\n\n\n@hesterbruikman could you suggest something here?",
